title: Re:Group Training
body:
Community group facilitators and hosts, as well as any community group members who are interested, are invited for an evening of training, discussion, and brainstorming. Leadership desires that this event be structured to serve you, so when prompted on the registration form, please list any/all questions and concerns you have regarding community groups. The content of the training will be based on your submissions.

Dinner will be provided. Families will be responsible for securing their own childcare. Reimbursement of $30 will be paid to families who indicate their need on the registration form.

title: Liz Vice Concert
body:
Liz Vice

Hosted by DPC

Tickets: $15 via online registration (click below); $20 at the door

All seating will be general admission; doors will open at 6 pm.

REGISTER

Liz Vice is a musician best known for her Gospel, soul, and R&B-infused album entitled, “There’s A Light”.

If you're not familiar with her, please enjoy this sample.

Raised in Portland, Oregon, and a recent resident of Brooklyn, New York, Ms. Vice has shared the stage with artists such as Cody Chesnutt, St. Paul and the Broken Bones, The Temptations, Lecrae, Eric Early of (Blitzen Trapper), Josh Garrels, The Wood Brothers, Tunde Baiyewu (Lighthouse Family), Luz Mendoza (Y La Bamba), Eshon Burgundy (Humble Beast), and many more.

With over one million Spotify listens of title track, “There’s A Light” from her first record, Liz Vice has been named ‘one to keep an ear out for’ in publications such as OPB’s One Song, World Cafe, eTown, NPR’s Live Wire, Relevant Magazine, and many podcast interviews. Vice has also been a featured artist in Portland at events such as Safeway Waterfront Blues Festival, Moon River, Forecastle, Portland Soundcheck, Soul’d Out Music Festival, Siren Nation Music Festival, Music on Main Street and more.

No matter how large the venue, her genuine approach to her artistry and playful interaction with the audience makes everyone feel like they're sitting at home on the couch watching a friend sing their heart out.

Having overcome many personal obstacles, she credits her adventurous life to not forcing anything. “It’s all about risk, and taking risk is never regretful…well, most of the time.”
